To extract the argument "What is life?" from the variable "/newtopic What is life?", you can use string manipulation functions. One way to achieve it in JavaScript could be:

```
let variable = "/newtopic What is life?";
let argument = variable.substring(variable.indexOf(" ") + 1);
```

This code first finds the index of the first space character in the string using `indexOf()`. Then, it extracts the substring from that position plus one until the end of the string using `substring()`. The resulting `argument` would be the string "What is life?".

